        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:50PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 250 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Waleska, or 7 miles
northwest of Canton, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, up to penny sized hail and frequent
cloud to ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Nelson, Sequoyah Lake, Lake Arrowhead, Talona, Waleska, Marblehill,
Talking Rock, Jasper, Salacoa Valley, Blaine, Lake Tamarack,
Talmadge, Tate, Canton, Hinton, and Ball Ground.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
